    <div>
        <h1>
            Our History
        </h1>
    </div>
    <div class="mainSectionText">
        <p>
            In the summer of 2019, Sarah Chen discovered Uncle Bob's River Farm during an accidental detour, where she encountered Robert "Uncle Bob" Henderson's remarkable coffee roasting operation.
            The retired farmer had spent decades perfecting his craft, cultivating coffee plants in custom greenhouses, and developing unique roasting techniques. Inspired by his methods and passion,
            Sarah apprenticed under Uncle Bob for six months, learning the intricacies of coffee cultivation and roasting.
        </p>
        <p>
            Cofe opened its doors in early 2020, bringing Uncle Bob's artisanal approach to an urban setting.
            The converted brownstone space featured reclaimed wood from the farm and a small greenhouse, creating an atmosphere that honored its rural origins.
            Despite launching just before the pandemic, Cofe's streamlined takeout model and innovative coffee subscription service helped it thrive during uncertain times.
        </p>
        <p>
            The shop's signature River Farm Blend, created using Uncle Bob's proprietary three-roast method, quickly gained popularity among coffee enthusiasts.
            Today, Cofe continues its partnership with Uncle Bob's farm, exclusively using his roasting techniques and bean selections.
            Uncle Bob, though in his eighties, still makes monthly visits to share his expertise and stories with customers, ensuring that the legacy of his craft lives on through every cup served at Cofe.
        </p>
    </div>


    <div >
