        <h1>
            Our Coffee
        </h1>
    </div>
    <div class="mainSectionText">
        <p>
            Our Coffee began as a dream shared between three friends who met in culinary school back in 2018. Maria, Dex, and Kai spent late nights perfecting recipes and roasting techniques.
            They started with a small cart in the local farmers' market, where their unique cardamom-spiced latte quickly became a neighborhood favorite.
            Each weekend brought new regulars and familiar faces.
            The cart evolved into a cozy storefront in 2020, nestled in an old bookstore that still had its original hardwood floors and exposed brick walls.
            The space seemed to tell its own stories.
            The pandemic posed challenges, but their commitment to community never wavered. They began delivering coffee beans by bicycle and hosting virtual brewing workshops.
        </p>
        
        <p>
            Today, Our Coffee serves as both a caf√© and a gathering space, where local artists display their work and musicians perform on Sunday mornings.
            The original cardamom latte remains their bestseller.
            Their roasting operation has expanded to supply beans to other local businesses, but they maintain their founding principle: every cup should tell a story and create a connection.
            The three friends still work behind the counter regularly, experimenting with new flavors and greeting customers by name.
            Their latest creation is a honey-lavender cold brew.
            Every morning, the smell of fresh coffee and baked goods draws people in from blocks away, making Our Coffee feel like everyone's second home.
        </p>
